{
    "name": "Forsaken Defender",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any ruins (Cheliax or Rahadoum)<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, squad (2\u201310), or company (12\u201324 forsaken arbalesters, defenders, and foot soldiers)<br/><b>Treasure</b> standard (hide armor, heavy pick, short sword)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Phantom Trench (Su)</b> Three times per day as a full-round action, a forsaken defender can create an extradimensional trench, as <i>create pit</i><sup>APG</sup> (Reflex DC 14 avoids), except the pit must be in a contiguous shape made of up to four 5-foot squares. The pit is 10 feet deep and persists for 4 rounds. The save DC is Intelligence-based.<br/><br/><b>Phantom Wall (Su)</b> Three times per day as a standard action, a forsaken defender can create a wall from loose rocks and bricks, as <i>wall of stone</i>, except the maximum area of the wall is 20 feet and the wall is always 10 feet high and 1 inch thick. The wall persists for 4 rounds."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Long ago, these defense specialists planned and supervised the construction of field fortifications for the Jistka Imperium. Now powered by unholy energies, they can create impromptu defenses in the blink of an eye."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This undead soldier carries a heavy-looking pickaxe in one hand and a short sword in the other.</i>",
